The paper discusses Hamilton-Jacobi-Isaacs (HJI) reachability analysis, which is commonly used in the field of control systems (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.RO) for safety analysis of autonomous systems. The paper also mentions the use of optimization techniques (cs.AI) and compares the performance of different methods (cs.LG, cs.MA).
